### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

Hi,

I don't know if there was already a feature request discussion about this - I couldn't find one.

Sometimes you have a component that gets several `@Input()`s but if one of them isn't passed to the component when it's called you would prefer if this code **won't even compile**. 

```typescript

export class VehicleCardComponent implements OnInit, OnDestroy {

  @Input() crewId: string;
  @Input() somData: string;
  
  ngOnInit(): void {
  }
  ngOnDestroy(): void {
  }
  
}
  
  ```
  
  Currently if the component doesn't get the `crewId` input nothing happens.

```html
<app-vehicle-card
  [somData]="'Hello'"
>
</app-vehicle-card>
  ```

  I thought about this after using other frameworks, e.g. **React**:
  
  
```tsx
interface CardProps {
  title: string,
  paragraph: string
}

export const Card = ({ title, paragraph }: CardProps) => {

return (
  <aside>
    <h2>{ title }</h2>
    <p>
      { paragraph }
    </p>
  </aside>
)};

```

If I call the `Card` component without providing `title` and `paragraph` my code won't compile.

### A small note
This is not the purpose of this issue but:

When declaring members in `strict-mode` you many times get this error when you don't assign an initial value:
_**Property 'something' has no initializer and is not definitely assigned in the constructor.**_

Perhaps using a required `@Input()` could make the compiler ignore this specific line cause I would know for certain that this input will be initialized. 

### Proposed solution

Disclaimer: I am not an Angular/JS/TS expert. 
There are a few possible solutions for this, I believe the most comfortable one would be to use something like 

```javascript

@RequiredInput() val: string;

// or
@MandatoryInput() val: boolean;

```

whenever we need one.

### Alternatives considered

There are other solutions that I found in Stack Overflow: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/35528395/make-directive-input-required

### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

forms

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

I've this custom type FormRawValue that returns the JSON/RawValue of any AbstractControl:

```
import { AbstractControl } from '@angular/forms';
export type FormRawValue<T extends AbstractControl> = T extends AbstractControl<any, infer TRawValue> ? TRawValue : never;
```

and this simple `IPerson` interface:

```
import { FormControl, FormGroup } from '@angular/forms';
import { FormRawValue } from './Forms.type';

export interface IPerson {
  id: FormControl<number>;
  name: FormControl<string>;
}

export type Person = FormRawValue<FormGroup<IPerson>>;
```

In the component code, I've a function that creates a new FormGroup using the JSON rawValue provided to it like this:

```
public map(data: Person) { // Person is simply the rawValue of IPerson

    let group = this._formBuilder.group<IPerson>(data as any); // works fine but bad appraoch
    let group1 = this._formBuilder.group<IPerson>(data); //ERROR here, but it should work because 'data' holds exactly the same thing that formBuilder is expecting.
  }
```

