### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

forms

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

The `FormBuilder.array()` method is usually used like this:
```ts
type MovieFormGroup = FormGroup<{ type: FormControl<'movie'>, title: FormControl<string> }>
// works great
const movies = fb.array<MovieFormGroup>([])
//    ^? FormArray<FormGroup<{ type: FormControl<'movie'>, title: FormControl<string> }>>
movies.push(fb.group({ type: 'movie', title: '' }))
const moviesValue = movies.value;
//    ^? Array<Partial<{ type: 'movie', title: '' }>>
```

Now let's consider that we want movies or books. We can use a union type, but that sadly brokes the type inference:
```ts
// let's use a union type, because we want movies or books
type BookFormGroup = FormGroup<{ type: FormControl<'book'>, title: FormControl<string> }>
// sadly this breaks the types
const items = fb.array<MovieFormGroup | BookFormGroup>([])
//    ^? FormArray<FormRecord<AbstractControl<any, any>>> which is incorrect
items.push(fb.group({ type: 'movie', title: '' }));
items.push(fb.group({ type: 'show', title: '' })); // should not compile but does
const itemsValue = items.value;
//    ^? Array<Partial<{ [x]: string: any }>>
```

